4 HJR___ COMMENDING REPRESENTATIVE TERRI COLLINS ON HER
5 ACCOMPLISHED CAREER OF SERVICE.
6
7 WHEREAS, on the eve of the conclusion of
8 Representative Terri Collins' long and distinguished
9 legislative career, it is both fitting and proper to recount
10 her many accomplishments and contributions to the State of
11 Alabama; and
12 WHEREAS, Representative Terri Collins was raised in
13 Birmingham and attended The University of Alabama, where she
14 earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Marketing; she
15 married her beloved husband and resided in Chattanooga
16 before moving to Decatur in 1982; and
17 WHEREAS, she worked for sixteen years in the banking
18 industry as Vice President of Marketing and Sales before
19 being elected to the Alabama House of Representatives in
20 2010, handily defeating her Democratic opponent with 56
21 percent of the vote; she was a member of the historic
22 freshman class that secured Republican control of the
23 Legislature for the first time in 136 years and helped usher
24 in the supermajorities that continue to this day; and
25 WHEREAS, Representative Collins began serving on the
26 Education Ways and Means Committee in 2011 and was first
27 appointed Chair of the Education Policy Committee in 2015;
28 and
Page 1

and
HJR196 INTRODUCED
29 WHEREAS, since taking office, Representative Collins
30 has sponsored and successfully carried numerous significant
31 pieces of legislation, including, but by no means limited
32 to, the Alabama Human Life Protection Act, the Alabama
33 Literacy Act, the Alabama School Choice and Student
34 Opportunity Act, Erin's Law, the Alabama College and Career
35 Readiness Act, and the Alabama Rural Hospital Investment Act
36 of 2025; and
37 WHEREAS, among her other notable legislative
38 achievements are the creation of the Alabama Workforce
39 Council; passage of the state's Good Samaritan law providing
40 civil immunity to individuals who voluntarily render
41 emergency assistance; and enactment of a measure requiring
42 only gun show promoters, rather than individual vendors, to
43 obtain a business license; and
44 WHEREAS, throughout her legislative service, she
45 secured substantial state funding for senior centers,
46 schools, parks, pre-K programs, nonprofits, and other
47 essential services within her legislative district; and
48 WHEREAS, she was appointed by the Speaker of the
49 House of Representatives to serve on the Women's Commission
50 and the School Safety Advisory Commission, which she
51 chaired, as well as the Education Committee of the Southern
52 Legislative Conference; she also served as Chair of the
53 Education Policy Committee of the National Conference of
54 State Legislators; and
55 WHEREAS, she was appointed by the Governor to the
56 Alabama Workforce Development Board and the Southern
Page 2

Alabama Workforce Development Board and the Southern
HJR196 INTRODUCED
57 Regional Education Board, where she also served as Chair;
58 and notably, she served as Chair of the Child Abuse and
59 Neglect Prevention Board; and
60 WHEREAS, ever close to Representative Collins' heart
61 has been her commitment to community service, including
62 service as Chair of the Tennessee Valley Caucus; service on
63 the Board of Directors of the Volunteer Center of Morgan
64 County and the Decatur Morgan Hospital Board; as a founding
65 member and Chair of the Women's Leadership Council and the
66 Morgan County Giving Circle of the Women's Foundation in
67 Decatur; and as President of the Decatur Rotary Club; and
68 WHEREAS, Representative Collins credits much of her
69 personal and legislative success to the constant support and
70 encouragement from her late husband, Tom, who was an active
71 and beloved figure in the Decatur community; together, they
72 were blessed with three children: Tracie Collins McPhillips
73 (Joseph), Tricia Collins, and Taylor Collins, and two
74 cherished grandchildren; and
75 WHEREAS, although the gentlelady from Decatur has
76 announced that she will not seek reelection to the House of
77 Representatives seat she has so honorably held for sixteen
78 years, she departs the public spotlight secure in the
79 knowledge that her work in Montgomery has strengthened the
80 protections afforded to unborn life, transformed public
81 education through higher standards and accountability,
82 strengthened the state's workforce, and expanded parental
83 choice in how Alabama's children are educated; and
84 WHEREAS, this body knows that her dedication to
Page 3

WHEREAS, this body knows that her dedication to
HJR196 INTRODUCED
85 service will not conclude when she leaves these hallowed
86 chambers but will continue in new and meaningful ways for
87 the benefit of her fellow Alabamians and all those she
88 serves; now therefore,
89 BE IT RESOLVED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA, BOTH
90 HOUSES THEREOF CONCURRING, That State Representative Terri
91 Collins is hereby highly commended and honored for sixteen
92 years of faithful and effective service to the people of the
93 State of Alabama and the future of this great state.
94 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, That a copy of this
95 resolution be presented to Representative Terri Collins as a
96 lasting token of the Legislature's profound gratitude,
97 admiration, and congratulations upon the conclusion of her
98 distinguished service in the Alabama House of
99 Representatives.
